# Easy Genomics — project context

Read [CLAUDE.md](../../CLAUDE.md) for full detail. This rule captures what Graphify cannot infer.

## Monorepo

- `packages/back-end` — Lambdas + CDK
- `packages/front-end` — Nuxt 3 SPA (Pinia, `@nuxt/ui`)
- `packages/shared-lib` — Zod schemas, types, OpenAPI generator, shared constructs

## Who owns what (back-end)

| Question about… | Look in |
| --------------- | ------- |
| Labs, orgs, users, app-level runs, files, uploads, data collections, tags | `back-end/.../easy-genomics/` |
| AWS HealthOmics workflows/runs | `back-end/.../aws-healthomics/` |
| Seqera / Nextflow Tower | `back-end/.../nf-tower/` |
| API contract / route list | `shared-lib/src/app/openapi/` (generated YAML + `route-schemas.ts`) |
| Auth checks | `back-end/src/app/utils/auth-utils.ts` |
| HTTP errors | `shared-lib/src/app/utils/HttpError.ts` + `buildErrorResponse` |

## Front-end API layer

HTTP calls live in `front-end/src/app/repository/modules/` (`labs.ts`, `omics-runs.ts`, `seqera-runs.ts`, `data-collections.ts`, …), not in Vue components.

## Handler shape

Thin `*.lambda.ts` → Zod validate → `auth-utils` → `*Service` → `buildResponse` / `buildErrorResponse`. No AWS SDK in handlers.

## Docs worth opening for non-code questions

| Topic | Path |
| ----- | ---- |
| Upgrade hazard (DynamoDB) | `docs/deployment/upgrading.md` |
| Local back-end dev | `docs/development/local-backend-dev.md` |
| Contributing / branches | `docs/development/contributing.md` |
| Graphify setup | `docs/development/graphify.md` |

## When exploring code

Use Graphify (rule `graphify.mdc` or MCP server `graphify`) **before** wide Grep/Glob. Ask structural questions as graph queries, e.g. `"path from create-laboratory-run to HealthOmics"`.

After you change `.ts` / `.vue` files, run `graphify update .` if the graph may be stale.
